From: Peios <kernel@peios.org>
Subject: FACS patch 12: f_mode fixup for KACS-native open

After security_file_open() fires in do_dentry_open(), call
kacs_fixup_open_fmode() so KACS can override f_mode from the
granted mask. This enables execute-only handles (FILE_EXECUTE
without FILE_READ_DATA) which have no VFS open flag equivalent.

Guarded by CONFIG_SECURITY_PKM. When KACS is not built, the
call compiles away entirely.

--- a/fs/open.c
+++ b/fs/open.c
@@ -954,6 +954,13 @@
 	error = security_file_open(f);
 	if (unlikely(error))
 		goto cleanup_all;
+
+#ifdef CONFIG_SECURITY_PKM
+	/* KACS-native open: fix f_mode from granted mask (§14.3 patch 12).
+	 * No-op when kacs_open_desired == 0 (all legacy opens). */
+	extern void kacs_fixup_open_fmode(struct file *f);
+	kacs_fixup_open_fmode(f);
+#endif

 	/*
 	 * Call fsnotify open permission hook and set FMODE_NONOTIFY_* bits
